texts.text: Whoa, everyone stop. That thing over there...
>Gakuto points towards some glowing particles rising from the ground.
A demon's corpse?
A rare item?
Yeah. The ones from earlier were like that too.
It just seemed different from usual.
Well... It's pretty but I wouldn't get my hopes up.
Look closer. It's a demon's corpse.
And they're everywhere too. Kinda gross.
They haven't been like this for long either.
There's probably something even stronger waiting for us up ahead.
What should we do? Go back a find another way?
...Nah, let's keep goin'.
We need to stay on the offensive against an opponent like this.
Yo, we're lucky enough to know that she's up ahead too.
Roger. Stay sharp and ready to summon.
(Yo, everyone stop! Look...)
>Among the corpses of demons, one appears to be dawdling leisurely.
(So many demons, all at once?)
(Even the stronger ones are dead. What do we do?)
I know you're hiding over there, humans.
How much longer must I leave myself so open like this?
Just staring won't get you anywhere.
Shit... She's on to us.
Well, that's one way to greet someone I suppose...
...and a surprise attack on top of that. How pathetic!
>The arrow of light that was heading towards Tzitzimitl vanishes.
That arrow of light...!
All with such dreadful manners, especially as the guests here.
Isn't that right, Marici?
...Ugh.
Marici! So that means she's...
Yes, she is Tzitzimitl.
Ha... So you've finally come out to play.
I was wondering when you'd show yourself.
While we're at it, let's make this more festive by calling my minions.
Bring it on!
Just try!
No!
Don't... You mustn't be goaded so easily.
...What do you mean?
I also was too late to understand.
The demons that are vanquished in here evaporate and rise to the heavens.
And all that die here turn into those stars.
They become the source of her power... As sacrifices.
What?
The stars visible around the eclipse...
They're the manifestation of her powers, and also her dark fairy minions.
As the number of stars grows, so do her powers.
And she's even having her minions hunt down more demons.
Oh, I guess you did figure it out... That's too bad...
I see...
Even if her minions die, they still turn back into stars.
She was trying to trick us into making her stronger.
And she also wanted us to take down anything her minions couldn't.
Did I miss anything?
We cannot allow her to become even stronger. I must defeat you right here!
*Snicker*
Ever the optimist. And so brave for a goddess.
But that doesn't' explain why you've shown yourself.
If you really wished to kill me, you'd have stayed hidden...
I mean, wouldn't it be so much easier to go after me from the shadows?
*Wince*
It's not that you want to but rather you can't?
What?
The sun god and his valiant goddess, Marici.
In reality, no one should ever be able to see you.
But all you need to do is lookup.
I've already taken over half of the precious light you need.
Your power wanes as mine grows.
...Am I wrong?
...Silence. That alone will not bring me down.

*Laughs*
How cute, and so stubborn.
Like I said. I was waiting for you to show yourself.
No more surprise attacks coming from you...
You being here is enough proof of that.
I'll be going now.
Wait...
Stop her!
...Oh? You plan to take me on?
Exactly. You're facing us now, yo!
*Laugh*
Me face you? I can't be bothered.
Wha...!
Humans are just pathetic creatures doomed to be destroyed by me.
Your fate will come in due time, so there's no need to hurry things.
Go, before I change my mind.
No way we're letting you go! Devil Download!
Oh my... You wish to fight that much?
In that case, I'll tell my minions to focus on you.
I still have things to do, so enjoy.
If you happen to find me later, then I'll come out to play.
Bye.
Crap! Wait...!
>Tzitzimitl melds into the darkness and vanishes...
Shit... She's not taking us seriously at all.
This won't do... We cannot allow her to grow any stronger...!
Ah, wait, Marici...!
>Marici ignores any pleas to stop and flies off...
And she leaves us in the dark. So, what should we do now?
We need to find and take down Tzitzimitl. That's all we can do, right?
The more demons we kill, the stronger Tzitzimitl gets.
You understand that, yes?
I know.
Or do you want to leave here and hope Marici can deal with this?
Ain't no way any of us are doin' that, yo.
I know, but it's just...
It doesn't matter if the demons want to keep fighting each other.
Our time is running out whether we like it or not.
We need to keep doing what we can.
...Right. Yes, we need to hurry.
Aight, let's get us a Tzitzimitl!
